problems: High congestion on both 2.4GHz (5 networks) and 5GHz (6 networks) bands.
Multiple overlapping channels, particularly on 2.4GHz channels 1 and 11.
Placement of the router may not be optimal (near bedroom window).
No recent speed test results for download/upload confirmation.
fixes: Change the 2.4GHz channel to 6 for reduced interference (currently 11 and 1 are crowded).
Switch the 5GHz channel to 149 for better performance (current channels 36 and 157 are congested).
Consider repositioning the router to a more central location within the home to improve coverage.
Disable any unused devices from the network to alleviate congestion.
Enable QoS settings (if available) to prioritize gaming traffic.
